headline" class=3D"text-gray-900 font-bold leading-rem30px text-rem25px bp6=
00:text-rem32px bp600:leading-rem38px mt-rem32px mb-rem16px break-words  ">=
What is a menstrual cycle?</h3><p data-identity=3D"paragraph-element" class=
=3D"text-gray-800 my-rem16px text-rem19px leading-rem34px  ">The menstrual =
cycle is a term to describe the sequence of events that occur in your body =
as it prepares for the possibility of pregnancy each month. Your menstrual =
cycle is the time from the first day of your menstrual period until the fir=
st day of your next menstrual period. Every person=E2=80=99s cycle is sligh=
tly different, but the process is the same.</p><h3 data-identity=3D"headlin=
e" class=3D"text-gray-900 font-bold leading-rem30px text-rem25px bp600:text=
-rem32px bp600:leading-rem38px mt-rem32px mb-rem16px break-words  ">How lon=
g is a normal menstrual cycle?</h3><p data-identity=3D"paragraph-element" c=
lass=3D"text-gray-800 my-rem16px text-rem19px leading-rem34px  ">The averag=
e length of a menstrual cycle is 28 days. However, a cycle can range in len=
gth from 21 days to about 35 days and still be normal.</p><h4 data-identity=
=3D"headline" class=3D"text-gray-900 font-bold leading-rem24px text-rem20px=
 bp600:text-rem25px bp600:leading-rem30px mt-rem32px mb-rem16px break-words=
  ">How many days between periods is normal?</h4><p data-identity=3D"paragr=
aph-element" class=3D"text-gray-800 my-rem16px text-rem19px leading-rem34px=
  ">The days between periods is your menstrual cycle length. The average me=
nstrual cycle lasts 28 days. However, cycles lasting as little as 21 days o=
r as long as 35 days can be normal.</p><div data-identity=3D"billboard-ad" =
class=3D"flex bp1100:hidden print:hidden max-w-[400px] min-w-[300px] m-auto=
 items-center justify-center bg-gray-300 pt-rem16px pb-[3.125rem] my-rem32p=
x  "><div class=3D"max-w-[300px] mx-auto"><p class=3D"text-gray-800 upperca=
se text-rem10px leading-rem16px mx-auto w-fit">Advertisement</p><div class=
=3D"flex bp1100:hidden flex-col items-center justify-center"><div data-iden=
tity=3D"ad-slot" id=3D"billboard2_300x250_mobile" class=3D"ad-reset w-[300p=
x] !min-h-[250px] flex bg-gray-300"></div></div></div></div><h3 data-identi=
ty=3D"headline" class=3D"text-gray-900 font-bold leading-rem30px text-rem25=
px bp600:text-rem32px bp600:leading-rem38px mt-rem32px mb-rem16px break-wor=
ds  ">How long does a normal period last?</h3><p data-identity=3D"paragraph=
-element" class=3D"text-gray-800 my-rem16px text-rem19px leading-rem34px  "=
>Most people have their period (bleed) for between three and seven days.</p=
><h4 data-identity=3D"headline" class=3D"text-gray-900 font-bold leading-re=
m24px text-rem20px bp600:text-rem25px bp600:leading-rem30px mt-rem32px mb-r=
em16px break-words  ">Is a three-day period normal?</h4><p data-identity=3D=
"paragraph-element" class=3D"text-gray-800 my-rem16px text-rem19px leading-=
rem34px  ">A period is normal if it=E2=80=99s anywhere between three and se=
ven days. While on the shorter end of the range, some people have a menstru=
al period for three days. This is OK.</p><h3 data-identity=3D"headline" cla=
ss=3D"text-gray-900 font-bold leading-rem30px text-rem25px bp600:text-rem32=
px bp600:leading-rem38px mt-rem32px mb-rem16px break-words  ">What are the =
four phases of the menstrual cycle?</h3><p data-identity=3D"paragraph-eleme=
nt" class=3D"text-gray-800 my-rem16px text-rem19px leading-rem34px  ">The r=
ise and fall of your hormones trigger the steps in your menstrual cycle. Yo=
ur hormones cause the organs of your reproductive tract to respond in certa=
in ways. The specific events that occur during your menstrual cycle are:</p=
><ul data-identity=3D"unordered-list" class=3D"my-rem16px mx-0 pl-[1.25rem]=
 list-disc marker:text-brandBlue-500 marker:pl-rem24px  "><li class=3D"mb-r=
em12px pl-rem12px text-gray-800 text-rem19px leading-rem34px "><strong>The =
menses phase: </strong>This phase begins on the first day of your period. I=
t's when the lining of your uterus sheds through your vagina if pregnancy h=
asn=E2=80=99t occurred. Most people bleed for three to five days, but a per=
iod lasting only three days to as many as seven days is usually not a cause=
 for worry.</li><li class=3D"mb-rem12px pl-rem12px text-gray-800 text-rem19=
px leading-rem34px "><strong><a data-identity=3D"link" href=3D"https://my.c=
